OL,4,CAlmost a quarter of England's pupils
OL,5,Cout of school
OL,6, Almost a quarter (23.3%) of pupils in
OL,7, England were out of school last week,
OL,8, the latest official attendance figures
OL,9, show.
OL,11,FThis means there were 1.7 million
OL,12,Fpupils absent, up from 1.5 million the
OL,13,Fweek before.
OL,15,FThe latest figures include over a
OL,16,Fmillion off for Covid-related reasons,
OL,17,Fbut only 47,000 actually had Covid.
OL,19,FIn secondary schools, the absence rate
OL,20,Fwas nearer a third (32.7%) of pupils,
OL,21,Fwhile in primaries it was 17%.
